ucsc_dining.name: Owl's Nest Cafe
ucsc_dining.description: Check out the Express Store located at Quarry Plaza right next to the Bay Tree Bookstore. The Express Store has a variety of teas, coffees, sandwiches, drinks, snacks, breakfast foods, pastries, and a host of convenience items.

ucsc_dining.name: Banana Joe's
ucsc_dining.description: Located near the Crown College fountain this cafe/convenience store offers burgers, sandwiches, coolers stocked with grab-and-go meals, espresso drinks, groceries and plenty of variety.

ucsc_dining.name: Perk Coffee @ Baskin Engineering
ucsc_dining.description: Perk Coffee Bars offer 100% organic coffee and a wide selection of freshly baked muffins, Bagelry bagels, and pastries. Stop by for a latte or mocha, or meet friends for a quick lunch from the selection of salads, sandwiches or sushi offered at most locati

ucsc_dining.name: Porter Kresge Dining Hall
ucsc_dining.description: Serving the west side of campus, this dining hall features a remodeled serving area made with natural, sustainable textures and surfaces. Come enjoy the patio, perched high on the hill overlooking the bay.

ucsc_dining.name: College Eight/Oakes Dining Hall
ucsc_dining.description: Located near the West Field House, this dining hall features incredible views of the hillsides of Santa Cruz. This is also the home of The Bakery at Rachel Carson College, which supplies fresh-baked goods to all our locations.

ucsc_dining.name: College Eight Cafe
ucsc_dining.description: Located at Rachel Carson College. Serving made to order espresso coffee drinks, pastries, grab-and-go meals, local, organic ice cream by alumni-owned Mission Hill Creamery, and more.

ucsc_dining.name: Oakes Cafe
ucsc_dining.description: Located in the Oakes College community, this fun, funky café is the perfect spot for a grilled chicken sandwich or charbroiled burger. With its international surf theme and late night hours, Oakes Café is a popular student hangout—staff and faculty are wel

ucsc_dining.name: Global Village Cafe
ucsc_dining.description: Our menu features many delicious items including: Acai Bowl - blended with strawberries and bananas, with granola on top; free range eggs; all natural meat; and Gallo Pinto - a mix of rice, beans, and veggies with Lizano sauce from Costa Rica.

ucsc_dining.name: Bay Tree Express Store
ucsc_dining.description: Check out the Express Store located at Quarry Plaza right next to the Bay Tree Bookstore. The Express Store has a variety of teas, coffees, sandwiches, drinks, snacks, breakfast foods, pastries, and a host of convenience items.

ucsc_dining.name: Stevenson Coffee House
ucsc_dining.description: Located at Stevenson College. This long-standing favorite offers espresso drinks, made-to-order salads and sandwiches, their famous fudgies, and more.

ucsc_dining.name: Cowell/Stevenson Dining Hall
ucsc_dining.description: Located on the hill above the East Field, this dining hall features a fantastic view of the Monterey Bay, with outdoor patio dining available to capture the crisp ocean breezes.

ucsc_dining.name: Cowell Coffee Shop
ucsc_dining.description: The Cowell Coffee Shop offers delicious baked goods, chili, salads, sandwiches and more. It also exhibits student art shows. Cash, check, credit/debit cards, and flexi-dollars accepted.

ucsc_dining.name: Crown/Merrill Dining Hall
ucsc_dining.description: Serving the east side of campus, this dining hall boasts a 20-foot salad bar. Next door is Banana Joe’s, offering premium beverages, on-the-go menu selections, groceries, and convenient, natural foods to-go.

ucsc_dining.name: Terraa Fresca Restaurant & Coffee Bar
ucsc_dining.description: Enjoy an exquisite lunch at this full service restaurant, or visit the coffee bar for a quick bite. Located above the Colleges Nine & Ten Dining Hall.

ucsc_dining.name: College Nine and Ten Dining Hall
ucsc_dining.description: Nestled in the redwoods near the academic campus core, this is our largest dining hall. Upstairs, you’ll find Terra Fresca Restaurant and Coffee Bar, a popular spot for students to meet with faculty.

ucsc_dining.name: Perk Coffee @ University Center
ucsc_dining.description: Perk Coffee Bars offer 100% organic coffee and a wide selection of freshly baked muffins, Bagelry bagels, and pastries.

ucsc_dining.name: Vivas
ucsc_dining.description: Located at Merrill College, Vivas serves fresh, natural & organic mexican food.
